cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ClauseGuard: Interpretable Verification of LLM Outputs via Graph Tsetlin Machines"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Anwar
    affiliation: "University of Agder (UiA)"
abstract: >
  A symbolic audit layer that consumes LLM-generated atomic claim triples
  and a context knowledge graph, and emits per-claim Support/Refute/NEI
  labels with human-readable Boolean clauses and SAT-verifiable receipts.
  Targets EU AI Act Article 13 + 14 compliance for any LLM deployment.
date-released: 2026-05-23
license: MIT
keywords:
  - Tsetlin Machine
  - Graph Tsetlin Machine
  - LLM verification
  - hallucination detection
  - interpretable AI
  - EU AI Act
  - knowledge graph
  - counterfactual recourse
  - SAT verification
  - neuro-symbolic
